                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-22T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 22, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 22—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>539. Delegation’s 338, October 21, 8 p.m. I am informed by the Secretariat that
                    this communication is also being sent to the following states: Germany, Saudi
                    Arabia, Brazil, Costa Rica, Danzig, Egypt, Iceland, Japan, Liechtenstein,
                    Monaco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
